{"questionId":"9077099","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A uniform rod of weight 36.0 N and length 5.00 m rests horizontally. The rod is pivoted at its&nbsp;left-hand end and is supported at a distance of 4.00 m from the frictionless pivot.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/eb5e5b5f1d22e1718498c29a55eae7fda373709a.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>At the instant the rod becomes vertical&nbsp;show that the angular speed is <em>ω</em> = 2.43 rad s<sup>–1</sup>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«from conservation of energy» Change in GPE = Change in rotational KE ✔</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"W\\frac{L}{2} = \\frac{1}{2}I{\\omega ^2}\">\n  <mi>W</mi>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>L</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>I</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>ω</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\omega&nbsp; = \\sqrt {\\frac{{36.0 \\times 5.00}}{{30.6}}} \">\n  <mi>ω</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>36.0</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>5.00</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>30.6</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>«<em>ω</em>&nbsp;= 2.4254 rad s<sup>–1</sup>»</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077099","referenceCode":"18N.3.SL.TZ0.c.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"At the instant the rod becomes vertical show that the angular speed is ω = 2.43 rad s–1.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: Engineering physics (Core topics)","B.1 – Rigid bodies and rotational dynamics","Option B: Engineering physics","Option B: En